  "motivation": "Feature detection is a W3C TAG design principle and a tool that Web authors rely on for graceful degradation of their pages. Currently, the only way for web developers to detect support for CSS at-rules is to use JavaScript. This feature allows at-rule support to be detected using the same `@supports` feature used to detect support for CSS properties.",
